[SN]TITLE[SN]
Leaders from three faiths gather in Cardiff mosque

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Religious leaders from three faiths gathered in Cardiff for the first time on Thursday to "show solidarity of faith".

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Muslim Council of Wales said leaders from Judaism, Christianity and Islam visited Dar Ul-Isra mosque.
It aimed to show extremism and religious hatred have "no place" in the city.
More than 100 guests from the Jewish and Christian faiths visited the mosque.
